ğŸ¯ Project Objective
Configure storage using partitions + LVM, resize disks safely, mount permanently, and enforce disk quotas.



Check disk:
lsblk


ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Create Disk Partition
fdisk /dev/sdb



ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Create LVM Structure
1ï¸âƒ£ Create Physical Volume (PV)
pvcreate /dev/sdb1
pvdisplay


2ï¸âƒ£ Create Volume Group (VG)
vgcreate vg_data /dev/sdb1
vgdisplay

3ï¸âƒ£ Create Logical Volume (LV)
lvcreate -L 5G -n lv_app vg_data
lvdisplay

ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Create Filesystem
mkfs.ext4 /dev/vg_data/lv_app

ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Mount Logical Volume
mkdir /data


Mount:
mount  /dev/vg_data/lv_app  /data

Verify:
df -h



ğŸ”¹ Step 5: Permanent Mount (fstab)

vim /etc/fstab
/dev/vg_data/lv_app   /data   ext4   defaults   0 0

Test:
mount -a

ğŸ”¹ Step 6: Resize Logical Volume (Important Skill)


â• Extend LV (Live, no data loss)
lvextend -L +2G /dev/vg_data/lv_app


Resize filesystem:
resize2fs /dev/vg_data/lv_app

Verify:
df -h

ğŸ”¹ Step 7: Setup Disk Quotas
Install quota package
dnf install quota -y

vim /etc/fstab
/dev/vg_data/lv_app /data ext4 defaults,usrquota,grpquota 0 0

Remount:
mount -o remount /data

Create quota files
quotacheck -cug /data
quotaon /data

Step 8: Apply User Quota
Create test user:
useradd testuser
passwd testuser

Set quota:
edquota -u testuser

Example:
Soft limit: 500MB
Hard limit: 700MB

Check quota:
quota -u testuser



























